{"Body":"<p>Referring to <a href=\"http://english.stackexchange.com/questions/22357/equivalent-of-both-when-referring-three-or-more-items\">this question</a> it seems that English does not have the equivalent of \"both\" for three items. Although it would seem to be a useful word, I am unaware of its existence in any languages. Is there any language that has such a word?</p>\n", "Id":"2112", "FavoriteCount":"2", "Title":"Are there any languages with the equivalent of \"both\" for three items?", "CreationDate":"2012-06-15T01:14:14.983", "AnswerCount":"4", "PostTypeId":"1", "OwnerUserId":"1103", "Tags":"<historical-linguistics><cross-linguistic><comparative-linguistics>", "comments":[], "ViewCount":"366", "LastActivityDate":"2012-06-23T01:52:11.740", "Score":"10", "CommentCount":"4", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"4", "WebsiteUrl":"https://github.com/louismullie/", "Location":"Montr√©al, Canada", "Id":"1103", "DownVotes":"0", "AccountId":"1061058", "Views":"0", "Reputation":"151", "CreationDate":"2012-06-15T01:08:49.983", "DisplayName":"louism", "LastAccessDate":"2013-01-29T01:31:55.087", "Age":"23"}}